Grilled spicy salmonIINGREDIENTS:For the marinade:200 gms salmon, cut into two pieces2 tsp freshly ground black pepper25 gms piece fresh ginger, peeled and thinly sliced1 tbsp fish sauce½ tsp sugar1 tsp fresh lemon juice1 tsp crushed garlicTo garnish:1 tbsp chopped spring onion1/2 tsp red chilli flakesMETHODCombine the marinade’s ingredients in a bowl, add the salmon and rub evenly over it. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes.Grill the salmon on a charcoal grill (or gas barbecue) for about seven minutes on each side. Scatter the spring onion and chilli flakes over the salmon before serving.Chef Gajendra Singh is Executive Chef at the newly opened Unplugged Courtyard, Connaught Place. A result oriented professional, he has more than 16 years of experience in F&B operations. He has worked with various five star hotels.